Let $O = (0,0,1)$ be the center of the sphere, and let $X = (x,y,0)$ be a point on the boundary of the shadow.  Since $X$ is on the boundary, $\overline{PX}$ is tangent to the sphere; let $T$ be the point of tangency.  Note that $\angle PTO = 90^\circ.$  Also, lengths $OP$ and $OT$ are fixed, so $\angle OPT = \angle OPX$ is constant for all points $X$ on the boundary.

[asy]
